<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults have so far been recorded only in late spring and range in total length 10-12 mm and 3-4.5 mm in maximum width. In nearby Hong Kong, however, they have been observed throughout the summer and there larval food plants include 
<taxonomicName class="Tubothalamea" family="Milioliporidae" genus="Cucurbita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="Cucurbita moschata" order="Miliolida" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="moschata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Cucurbita moschata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Benincasa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Benincasa hispida" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="hispida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Benincasa hispida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Luffa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Luffa acutangula" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="acutangula">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Luffa acutangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Lagenaria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lagenaria siceraria" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="siceraria">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Lagenaria siceraria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yiu, V" journalOrPublisher="Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B161" refString="Yiu, V, 2009. Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1. Hong Kong Entomological Society, Hong Kong" title="Longhorn Beetles of Hong Kong. Insect Fauna of Hong Kong, Fascicle 1." year="2009">Yiu 2009</bibRefCitation>
). Elsewhere, larvae have also been found boring into stems of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Coccinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Coccinia indica" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Coccinia indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Luffa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Luffa aegyptiaca" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="aegyptiaca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Luffa aegyptiaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Trichosanthes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trichosanthes cucumerina" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cucumerina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Trichosanthes cucumerina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Beeson, CFC" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B8" refString="Beeson, CFC, 1941. The Ecology and Control of Forest Insects of India and the Adjoining Countries. Government of India Publication, Vasant Press, Dehradun, [xiii +] 1007 pp." title="The Ecology and Control of Forest Insects of India and the Adjoining Countries. Government of India Publication, Vasant Press, Dehradun, [xiii +] 1007 pp." year="1941">Beeson 1941</bibRefCitation>
; 
